  "transpose": true,
  "notes": "Source is Table B-2 (page 56), which lists termination/withdrawal rates by years of SERVICE only (no age dimension) for two groups: General and Safety. Rates are age-invariant in the source, so every target age row maps to the single service-based rate list. Transpose=true: printed rows are service years, which become target columns; printed columns (General/Safety) become the age dimension via copy. The document publishes separate General and Safety termination tables; the group-blend operation is not implemented, so mapping references the General group (the larger active headcount group, 3,608 vs 2,149 per Table A-4). Safety rates are transcribed but unblended - flag: Safety group rates are unused in mapping. Values are printed as percentages (values_unit=percent); numbers transcribed exactly as printed. Note: source service year 0 rate exists (10.00%/10.00%) but the target template excludes service year 0. Target column '6' = service years 5-6, '8' = 7-8, '10' = 9-10, '30' = 13-30, '40' = 31-40. Beyond service 20 the source has a flat '20+' rate (2.75% General), so target bins 30 (13-30) and 40 (31-40) use overlap_weighted with the flat tail rate for years beyond 20."
